tal Poynting flux in the observations is\nconsiderably larger than the vertical electromagnetic flux from previous\nobservational estimates. Therefore, our analysis confirms that the\nelectromagnetic energy flux in the photosphere is mainly horizontal and is most\nintense in localized regions along intergranular lanes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Mar 2022 16:27:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
