o display transient\nblue-shifted absorption. Decomposing the UV data into constant and variable\ncomponents, the blue-shifted absorption is associated with the former. This\nimplies that the outflow is not connect to the luminous flares in the data. The\njoint presence of UV and optical wind features reveals a multi-phase and/or\nstratified outflow from the outer disc. This type of persistent mass loss\nacross all accretion states has been predicted by radiation-hydrodynamic\nsimulations and helps to explain the shorter-than-expected outbursts duration.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Mar 2022 19:38:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-04"}
