 than that derived from our self-consistent\nmodel fit. We find that this difference may be due to disequilibrium chemistry,\nand the varying results between the models applied here demonstrate the\ndifficulty of constraining disequilibrium chemistry with low-resolution, low\nwavelength coverage data alone. Future work to combine observations from\nIGRINS, HST, and JWST will improve our estimate of the atmospheric composition\nof WASP-77Ab.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Mar 2022 00:18:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-18"}
