results of Schuberth et al. and Nguyen et al. at ultra-low\ntemperatures below $B_{\\rm N}$, along with those previously established at\nhigher temperatures in the paramagnetic state, provide compelling evidence that\nthe Kondo-destruction quantum criticality robustly drives unconventional\nsuperconductivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Mar 2022 10:19:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Apr 2022 08:57:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 27 Apr 2022 11:43:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-28"}
